# Base Development Standards

## Core Principles

- Small tasks, one at a time — baby steps
- TDD mandatory — failing tests BEFORE implementation
- Type Safety — all code fully typed
- Incremental Changes — focused changes over large modifications
- English Only — all code, docs, commits, schemas, configs
- NEVER `git push` without explicit user confirmation

## Code Review (MANDATORY)

Two steps before pushing: 1) `code-reviewer` agent 2) `review-before-push` workflow.

## Feature Pipeline

`plan-task` → `plan-backend/frontend-task` → `develop-backend/frontend` (TDD) → `code-reviewer` → `review-before-push` → push

PoC: `plan-poc` → `develop-poc` → verdict
